 The minister of healt Dr Zweli Mkhize confirmed on Saturday, September 5 2020 that South Africa’s COVID-19 cases now stands at 636 884, there has been 561 204 recoveries and 14 779 deaths. South Africa recorded an increase of 1 806 new cases since Friday 4 September 2020, when the countrys’ number cases stood at 635 078 14 678 deaths, according to the department of health. A total of 561 204 citizens have recovered, which brings the recovery rate to 88%. Dr Mkhize also announced that 101 patients have succumbed to COVID-19 during the past 24 hours. The new cases are: 45 from KwaZulu-Natal, 16 from Gauteng, 11 from Eastern Cape, 19 from Free State, 10 from Western Cape. This brings the total death toll in South Africa to 14 779. Xolile Mtshazo